# Nginx Configurator

## Overview
Generate optimized Nginx configurations for various use cases.

## Activation
Activates when user mentions "nginx", "reverse proxy", "load balancer", or "web server config".

## Instructions

1. Determine use case:
   - Static file serving
   - Reverse proxy
   - Load balancing
   - SSL termination

2. Include:
   - Security headers
   - Gzip compression
   - Caching
   - Rate limiting

## Examples

**Input:** "nginx reverse proxy for node app"

**Output:**
```nginx
upstream backend {
    server localhost:3000;
    keepalive 32;
}

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;
    return 301 https://$server_name$request_uri;
}

server {
    listen 443 ssl http2;
    server_name example.com;

    ssl_certificate /etc/ssl/certs/example.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/ssl/private/example.key;
    ssl_protocols TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3;

    # Security headers
    add_header X-Frame-Options "SAMEORIGIN" always;
    add_header X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff" always;

    # Gzip
    gzip on;
    gzip_types text/plain application/json application/javascript;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }

    location /static {
        alias /var/www/static;
        expires 30d;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
    }
}
```
